## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Specialized Chat Template Handler

**Only file to modify:** `common/chat.cpp`

### Two changes required:

---

### 1. New handler function (insert before line 1634, after `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`)

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_content;
    bool        first_user = true;
    bool        bos_added  = false;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_content = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (!bos_added) {
                data.prompt += tmpl.bos_token();
                bos_added = true;
            }
            data.prompt += "[INST] ";
            if (first_user && !system_content.empty()) {
                data.prompt += system_content + "\n";
                first_user = false;
            }
            data.prompt += content + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

---

### 2. Detection block in `common_chat_try_specialized_template()` (before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690)

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
    src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
    LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
}
```

The `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` absence check is critical — it distinguishes this handler from the existing Ministral/Mistral Large 3 handler which requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` + `[TOOL_CALLS]` + `[ARGS]`.

